1
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:40,800
<i> I'm not a mistress.</i>

2
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:44,033
<i>Because first of all, I was his
wife before her.</i>

3
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:47,533
<i>I'm content with my
children, my grandchild,</i>

4
00:00:47,667 --> 00:00:51,467
<i> and my fiancé, Noah Salvador,</i>

5
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:53,300
<i> whom I will marry soon.</i>

6
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:56,133
<i>The official diagnosis
matched what I told you.</i>

7
00:00:56,267 --> 00:00:57,800
<i>What if we get a
second opinion?</i>

8
00:00:57,933 --> 00:00:59,000
<i> It's a waste of time.</i>

9
00:00:59,133 --> 00:01:00,667
<i> Is God punishing me?</i>

10
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,000
<i> Is this my karma?</i>

11
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:03,933
<i>Don't be too
hard on yourself.</i>

12
00:01:04,067 --> 00:01:06,267
<i> I wish I had died.</i>

13
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,533
<i>- Dad, don't say that.
- I wish I had died!</i>

14
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:10,700
<i> Dad!</i>

15
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,400
<i>Miss Felma, I have
sad and bad news.</i>

16
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:16,100
<i>Dad is already paralyzed
from the waist down.</i>

17
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:19,800
<i> Mom!</i>

18
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:21,400
<i>- Felma! Felma!
- Mom!</i>

19
00:01:21,533 --> 00:01:23,267
<i>I'm sorry for reading
the messages.</i>

20
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,467
<i>That's the reason why
you lost consciousness earlier.</i>

21
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,267
<i>Miss Felma
cares about you.</i>

22
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:30,633
<i>Would you like us
to call Miss Felma?</i>

23
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:33,767
<i> We can call her.</i>

24
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:34,833
<i> I won't call them again.</i>

25
00:01:34,967 --> 00:01:38,833
<i>And I also won't receive
any calls from them.</i>

26
00:02:16,033 --> 00:02:17,033
It won't stop.

27
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:20,833
It's either you accept the call
or reject the call.

28
00:02:26,867 --> 00:02:28,567
I wonder why she's
not answering.

29
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,067
I wonder what happened.

30
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,900
No, I won't answer it.

31
00:02:39,667 --> 00:02:40,500
Okay.

32
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,133
I know you want
to answer it.

33
00:02:43,767 --> 00:02:44,533
Answer it.

34
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:46,233
No.

35
00:02:46,367 --> 00:02:47,467
No, I said I won't answer.

36
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,567
I promised you.

37
00:02:50,967 --> 00:02:52,400
- Answer it.
- They'll eventually get tired.

38
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:53,867
They'll stop.

39
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,400
Answer it.

40
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:01,167
No.

41
00:03:04,567 --> 00:03:05,267
Hello?

42
00:03:08,567 --> 00:03:09,967
This is Noah Salvador.

43
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:11,900
Felma's fiancé.

44
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,300
Jessica, is your
father beside you?

45
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:18,600
Can he hear me?

46
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,267
Noah, please
give it to me.

47
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,533
Please give it to me.

48
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,933
Manuel, do you hear me?

49
00:03:31,167 --> 00:03:32,200
Do you remember me?

50
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:34,367
We met here in
the Philippines.

51
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:40,933
<i>- Mom!
- Felma! Stop!</i>

52
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:49,967
I won't fight you
or disrespect you.

53
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:53,600
In fact, I'm going
to ask you a favor.

54
00:03:55,067 --> 00:03:58,233
Please leave Felma
and me alone.

55
00:03:59,367 --> 00:04:00,667
We'll be getting
married soon.

56
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,300
Let's have a
man-to-man talk.

57
00:04:05,167 --> 00:04:08,600
What you and Felma had
is a thing of the past.

58
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:11,033
You can never
bring that back.

59
00:04:11,567 --> 00:04:14,500
You're already married
and have another family.

60
00:04:15,867 --> 00:04:18,367
Whatever happened
to you, I'm sorry.

61
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,900
And I hope you recover.

62
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:26,333
But stop involving Felma,
both of us,

63
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,267
and even the kids,
with what happened to you.

64
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,867
Felma deserves
to be happy.

65
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,100
And I intend to
make her happy.

66
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,000
So, please.

67
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,200
Leave us alone.

68
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:32,367
This is the right time
for us to get married.

69
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,700
We'll be a family.

70
00:05:34,867 --> 00:05:37,867
We're still a family even
if we don't get married.

71
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,167
I know.
But I want to marry you.

72
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:42,100
That's what I
dream for you.

73
00:05:42,233 --> 00:05:43,900
To marry you in a church.

74
00:05:44,033 --> 00:05:46,367
It's just a
waste of money.

75
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:47,633
It doesn't have
to be grand.

76
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:48,900
We can have
something simple.

77
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,300
What matters is
that we get married.

78
00:05:52,133 --> 00:05:54,500
Love, listen to me.

79
00:05:55,033 --> 00:05:56,267
I'm good.

80
00:05:56,933 --> 00:06:01,433
Now that we're having
a baby, my dream of us

81
00:06:01,567 --> 00:06:03,100
becoming a family is
finally happening.

82
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:05,100
That's enough for me.

83
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,000
That already
makes me happy.

84
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:16,833
Maybe we're going through this
because God is punishing us.

85
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:18,367
Because up until now, our
relationship still doesn't have

86
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,833
a blessing.

87
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:22,467
Come on, love.

88
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,900
Are we going to talk
about marriage right now?

89
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,333
I'm sorry, Dad.

90
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:38,767
I did not expect someone
else would take the call

91
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,600
for Miss Felma.

92
00:06:41,767 --> 00:06:42,700
Sorry.

93
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,467
You don't have to
say sorry, dear.

94
00:06:46,567 --> 00:06:50,133
It actually seems like it
turned out better to hear

95
00:06:50,267 --> 00:06:51,867
what Noah said.

96
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,100
How could you do that?

97
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,800
You didn't want
to answer it.

98
00:07:17,533 --> 00:07:18,567
So I did.

99
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:20,567
And as your fiancé,

100
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,500
I think I have the right
to put a stop

101
00:07:22,633 --> 00:07:24,033
to whatever Manuel's doing.

102
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:26,133
But he didn't do
anything wrong.

103
00:07:26,567 --> 00:07:27,267
Oh, really?

104
00:07:27,967 --> 00:07:29,667
So what do you call what's
happening between us?

105
00:07:30,567 --> 00:07:32,700
Isn't it hurting
our relationship?

106
00:07:34,133 --> 00:07:35,933
Because we argue
because of him?

107
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:41,567
Unless this relationship
really doesn't matter to you.

108
00:07:42,867 --> 00:07:45,000
Because you care more
about how he feels

109
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:47,333
than how I feel.

110
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:57,633
Why?

111
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:00,367
What do you
expect from me?

112
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:03,667
What am I expected feel?

113
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:08,867
I waited for years for you
to get ready

114
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,833
to enter a relationship with me.

115
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:14,967
I respected your phase.

116
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:17,833
I didn't rush you.

117
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,067
Unless you were just
forced to accept my feelings.

118
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:25,600
But still, you committed to me.

119
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:28,800
We are engaged.

120
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,500
We should be taking
care of our future.

121
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:35,700
But your past keeps
insisting on being part

122
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,367
of your present and future.

123
00:08:41,567 --> 00:08:42,733
Felma...

124
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:45,900
where do I fit in?

125
00:08:47,367 --> 00:08:48,467
What should I do?

126
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:51,167
What am I
supposed to feel?

127
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,033
Maybe it was wrong for me
to answer Manuel's call.

128
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:57,767
But I'm getting
hurt, Felma.

129
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,067
I'm just fighting
for my love for you.

130
00:09:03,033 --> 00:09:05,833
Why? Don't you want
to fight for me?

131
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:31,900
<i>Hello? This is Noah Salvador,
Felma's fiancé.</i>

132
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:35,533
<i>Please leave Felma
and me alone.</i>

133
00:09:35,667 --> 00:09:36,933
<i>We're getting
married soon.</i>

134
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:47,300
The lunch is almost done.

135
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:48,867
Are you going to eat at
the dining,

136
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,133
or do you want it brought here?

137
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:02,867
You didn't eat
breakfast again?

138
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:05,700
Do you want to get sick?

139
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:08,367
What's your problem?

140
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:11,000
Don't you like my cooking?

141
00:10:15,167 --> 00:10:18,900
Next time, tell me
if you don't want to eat.

142
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:22,200
So I won't get tired preparing
and cooking for you.

143
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:24,967
Don't you know that
my time is so limited?

144
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,700
I'm always rushing because
I don't want to be late.

145
00:10:28,300 --> 00:10:30,433
But after everything,
you're not going to eat?

146
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:33,867
You've wasted
food and my time.

147
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:13,000
Aren't you going inside?

148
00:11:15,067 --> 00:11:16,067
Maybe not.

149
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,533
Are we okay?

150
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,400
Noah?

151
00:11:30,867 --> 00:11:33,200
I think we need to give
each other some space.

152
00:11:35,533 --> 00:11:36,933
What do you mean?

153
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,467
Exactly that.

154
00:11:43,133 --> 00:11:44,033
That space.

155
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:47,533
Are you breaking up with me?

156
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:50,933
Are you calling off the wedding?

157
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:52,933
How about you?

158
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:55,667
Is that what you want?

159
00:11:58,133 --> 00:11:58,800
How about you?

160
00:12:00,667 --> 00:12:01,833
It's up to you.

161
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:28,367
Family.

162
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:29,700
Mom!

163
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:32,033
You're early.

164
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,300
Have you eaten?

165
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,400
- Let's eat, Mom.
- Good evening, everyone.

166
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:42,967
Hello, Pretty Mama.

167
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:45,600
This was unplanned, Mom.

168
00:12:45,733 --> 00:12:48,533
This is the only time
Tetay and Daisy are available.

169
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:50,233
Didn't Uncle Noah
bring you here, Mom?

170
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:54,033
He did.

171
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:57,367
But I suddenly
have a headache.

172
00:13:00,433 --> 00:13:01,700
I'm having a migraine.

173
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:03,967
So maybe I'll just
get some rest.

174
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:05,267
I just have to sleep.

175
00:13:05,833 --> 00:13:08,633
I thought we could play later.

176
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:13,233
I'll make it up to
you next time, dear.

177
00:13:13,633 --> 00:13:15,200
- Okay.
- Okay.

178
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,467
That's a promise.

179
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,033
Continue eating.

180
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,767
Pretty Mama, are you okay?

181
00:13:31,933 --> 00:13:32,867
Yes.

182
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:47,200
Come on, Hazel.

183
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:48,733
Join me.

184
00:13:50,033 --> 00:13:52,867
Go ahead. Finish your food.

185
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,300
I'll eat before I go.

186
00:13:56,867 --> 00:13:59,500
I've already
cooked your dinner.

187
00:13:59,633 --> 00:14:03,300
Tell Jessica to put it in
the microwave

188
00:14:03,433 --> 00:14:04,833
when she comes home from school.

189
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,700
You should eat before
you go to work.

190
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:07,500
Come on.

191
00:14:07,933 --> 00:14:09,700
I'll take care
of that later.

192
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:11,833
No need.

193
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:13,267
Just finish your food.

194
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,800
I'm almost done here.

195
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:21,367
- Come on. Join me.
- No!

196
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:22,367
Come on and eat.

197
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,533
- I said no. Wait.
- Come on.

198
00:14:26,033 --> 00:14:27,700
What's wrong
with you, Manuel!

199
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,067
Look!

200
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:31,300
Instead of being done
with my chores already,

201
00:14:31,433 --> 00:14:32,900
now I have to clean
that up, too.

202
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:35,600
Come on! I told you I can
handle.

203
00:14:35,733 --> 00:14:36,733
You're so stubborn.

204
00:14:37,233 --> 00:14:38,100
Gosh!

205
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:40,100
Instead of being able
to leave already,

206
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:41,300
it's taking even longer.

207
00:14:42,733 --> 00:14:45,100
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to.

208
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:48,133
I'm so late again.

209
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:49,733
I've already received
so many warnings

210
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:51,033
from the hospital.

211
00:14:51,167 --> 00:14:52,067
Because of my tardiness.

212
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,333
But what else can I do?

213
00:14:53,467 --> 00:14:55,267
There's still so much I
need to take care of here.

214
00:14:55,633 --> 00:14:56,767
Manuel, come on.

215
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:58,867
Please cooperate, will you?

216
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,867
You're not helping,

217
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,133
and you're just making things
harder.

218
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,633
Come on! I'm already exhausted
from the hospital,

219
00:15:02,767 --> 00:15:04,433
and when I get home,
I even get more exhausted.

220
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:05,800
I'm not a superwoman!

221
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:21,500
- Did you enjoy?
- I did.

222
00:15:22,033 --> 00:15:24,333
Dad, thank you so much
for the lovely dinner

223
00:15:24,467 --> 00:15:25,900
and quality time at your house.

224
00:15:26,033 --> 00:15:29,133
But it would've been happier
if Pretty Mama had joined us.

225
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:34,633
She's having a headache.

226
00:15:35,533 --> 00:15:37,200
Don't worry, dear.
There's still next time.

227
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:40,600
If only your mom would
agree to live with us,

228
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:42,867
then the three of us
could be together.

229
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,367
Dad, I'd love that!

230
00:15:45,067 --> 00:15:47,567
Mom, please agree.

231
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:51,433
Sweetie, it's not that easy.

232
00:15:51,767 --> 00:15:54,367
Because you and Dad haven't
gotten back together yet.

233
00:15:55,267 --> 00:15:56,733
Dad, you should really
give it your all

234
00:15:56,867 --> 00:15:58,467
in winning Mom back.

235
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:01,800
And Mom, please don't be
too hard to get, okay?

236
00:16:02,233 --> 00:16:04,200
So you and Dad can
be together again.

237
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:06,100
And we can all live in
Pretty Mama's house

238
00:16:06,233 --> 00:16:08,833
with Auntie Andrea and Auntie
Coleen.

239
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:12,367
And, of course,
with Didang.

240
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,300
You talk too much.

241
00:16:16,867 --> 00:16:17,900
Let's go.

242
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:19,067
Okay.

243
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:21,367
But, Dad, start
courting Mom.

244
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,200
Yes, dear. I got that.

245
00:16:30,467 --> 00:16:31,700
Tetay is right.

246
00:16:32,133 --> 00:16:34,167
We should have a timeline.

247
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:38,000
This courtship should
already be counting, you know.

248
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:41,500
You'd better think
carefully about that timeline

249
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,933
you're talking about.

250
00:16:43,367 --> 00:16:44,467
Let's go.

251
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:46,833
Tetay and I have to
go early tomorrow.

252
00:16:46,967 --> 00:16:49,567
Perfect! Because after I drop
Tetay off,

253
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,567
I'll be taking you next. I'll
drop you off at your office.

254
00:16:51,967 --> 00:16:53,233
What?

255
00:16:53,367 --> 00:16:55,467
That's out of the way
to your office.

256
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:59,100
Well, if that's the only way
to your heart...

257
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:01,233
Okay?

258
00:17:04,367 --> 00:17:05,233
You win.

259
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:06,833
Let's go.

260
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:31,000
Mom?

261
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:33,700
How are you?

262
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:35,800
Does your head still hurt?

263
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:41,933
Mom.

264
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:44,667
Go.

265
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,233
Vent it out.

266
00:17:47,267 --> 00:17:48,633
I know there's a problem.

267
00:17:54,233 --> 00:17:55,967
Your Uncle Noah.

268
00:17:57,733 --> 00:17:58,700
What?

269
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:00,233
Are you having a fight?

270
00:18:06,667 --> 00:18:08,300
I did something.

271
00:18:10,667 --> 00:18:13,100
I wanted to explain
and say sorry,

272
00:18:13,233 --> 00:18:17,500
but then he suddenly
told me that

273
00:18:18,667 --> 00:18:21,100
we should give each other
some space.

274
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:22,867
Space?

275
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:25,267
As in a break-up
or just a cool off?

276
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:28,100
And how long, Mom?

277
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:30,900
Wait, what did
you do, Mom?

278
00:18:35,933 --> 00:18:39,733
Mom, you know that it's normal
in a relationship

279
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:45,133
to have misunderstandings
and little arguments, right?

280
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,333
But I'm sure
that whatever happened,

281
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,567
you and Uncle Noah
will make up eventually.

282
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:53,567
He can't stay mad at you.

283
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,600
Andrea, sweetie...

284
00:18:58,867 --> 00:19:01,167
I don't know if there's still
going to be a wedding.

285
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:13,567
Well, even if I were in
Uncle Noah's position,

286
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,867
I'd honestly feel hurt too, Mom.

287
00:19:17,667 --> 00:19:20,100
Why do you even communicate
with that family?

288
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:21,367
With those people?

289
00:19:22,267 --> 00:19:26,067
I called them because...

290
00:19:27,133 --> 00:19:28,400
I wanted to fight with them.

291
00:19:28,867 --> 00:19:30,200
I let out what I was feeling.

292
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:31,400
That's it. Move on.

293
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,567
I've moved on already.

294
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:38,100
I'm just checking in.

295
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:41,267
There's probably nothing wrong

296
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:45,233
with just asking
how your dad is doing.

297
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:48,067
Mom, I don't care.

298
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,100
And besides- let's say,

299
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:53,433
what happened to him
is really sad, okay?

300
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:55,933
But we don't have
to get involved anymore.

301
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:58,933
You used to tell us often

302
00:19:59,067 --> 00:20:00,767
that he's no longer part
of our family.

303
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:01,933
And maybe...

304
00:20:02,767 --> 00:20:05,700
that's just karma for what he
did when he abandoned us.

305
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:08,067
Andrea, don't think like that.

306
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:10,467
He's still your father.

307
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:11,300
Before.

308
00:20:11,767 --> 00:20:13,000
But not anymore.

309
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:15,667
When he abandoned us,
he stopped being my father.

310
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,133
I've already forgotten
about him.

311
00:20:17,367 --> 00:20:19,400
And my dad is now Uncle Noah.

312
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:21,400
He's the one who's been there

313
00:20:21,533 --> 00:20:23,567
for us siblings all these years.

314
00:20:23,700 --> 00:20:24,967
He's become our dad.

315
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,267
That's why, Mom...

316
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:30,167
we want you to get married.

317
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:33,733
So we can finally
be a happy family.

318
00:20:37,533 --> 00:20:39,667
But what if the wedding
doesn't push through?

319
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:41,400
Mom, the question is...

320
00:20:43,667 --> 00:20:46,033
Do you really want to marry
Uncle Noah?

321
00:20:48,633 --> 00:20:51,067
Or would you just let the
two of you completely separate

322
00:20:51,733 --> 00:20:54,000
because you can't let go
of your ex?

323
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:19,133
What's that?

324
00:21:19,867 --> 00:21:21,100
It stinks!

325
00:21:22,667 --> 00:21:23,867
Manuel!

326
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:26,267
What's wrong with you?

327
00:21:26,933 --> 00:21:28,500
Why did you poop there?

328
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,333
I'm sorry.

329
00:21:30,467 --> 00:21:32,333
I didn't make it
to the bathroom in time.

330
00:21:32,467 --> 00:21:35,767
Why didn't you ask for help?
You would feel it.

331
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:38,133
You should've asked for help,
even if you had to shout.

332
00:21:38,767 --> 00:21:39,533
Jessica!

333
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:41,467
She already went to school.

334
00:21:42,167 --> 00:21:46,133
I don't want to bother you
because I know you're tired

335
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:48,067
and you got home late
from the hospital.

336
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:49,767
Oh, so now? What?

337
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:51,067
It's the same.

338
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:52,033
Isn't it?

339
00:21:52,167 --> 00:21:55,033
I'm still the one cleaning up
your mess.

340
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:57,400
Look. Come on!

341
00:21:57,633 --> 00:21:58,467
Look!

342
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:19,633
Mom?

343
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:21,267
Are you okay?

344
00:22:22,367 --> 00:22:23,700
Are you not feeling well?

345
00:22:24,167 --> 00:22:26,233
I had a snack earlier.
That's why...

346
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:28,833
That's why
I don't feel like eating.

347
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:33,633
Mom,

348
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:36,300
didn't Uncle Noah
bring you here?

349
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:40,000
Isn't Sinigang na Hipon
his favorite?

350
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,067
And Auntie Paz
was asking me earlier

351
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:46,033
why you and Uncle Noah
were ignoring each other.

352
00:22:46,167 --> 00:22:47,933
- Is that true, Mom?
- You're having an LQ, Mom?

353
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:49,733
LQ at their age?

354
00:22:49,867 --> 00:22:51,167
You're so mean.

355
00:22:51,300 --> 00:22:52,100
Why?

356
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:54,533
- You're so bad.
- It's worse than LQ.

357
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:02,000
Why, Andrea?

358
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:07,967
Uncle Noah asked for some space.

359
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:09,200
Space?

360
00:23:09,333 --> 00:23:10,533
Cool off?

361
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,067
That's for youngsters.

362
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:14,333
Isn't it a prank?

363
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:16,800
Who knows? Maybe it's a prank.

364
00:23:17,467 --> 00:23:18,900
Stop it.

365
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:21,433
The food's right in front of us.

366
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:23,867
Mom...

367
00:23:24,233 --> 00:23:25,567
just tell them the truth.

368
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:27,633
Tell them the real reason

369
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:33,400
why you and Uncle had a fight
that made him ask for space.

370
00:23:33,533 --> 00:23:35,000
Andrea, what do you mean?

371
00:23:36,333 --> 00:23:38,167
Mom, what is Andrea
talking about?

372
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:42,233
Mom?

373
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:48,067
What's going on?

374
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:53,167
Andrea, if Mom doesn't want to
talk, then you say it.

375
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,167
Because it's obvious
that you know.

376
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:57,700
Coleen and I
have the right to know.

377
00:23:57,833 --> 00:23:59,333
And we've already talked
about this, right?

378
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,333
Dear...

379
00:24:01,667 --> 00:24:02,733
don't.

380
00:24:02,867 --> 00:24:03,800
Don't say it.

381
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:07,167
Let's not make this bigger.

382
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:10,633
Uncle Noah caught Mom...

383
00:24:12,533 --> 00:24:14,333
checking on that guy
from Canada.

384
00:24:15,467 --> 00:24:18,400
The worthless man, her ex,
who abandoned us.

385
00:24:26,700 --> 00:24:29,000
I only did that because...

386
00:24:31,733 --> 00:24:33,900
your father
is becoming paralyzed.

387
00:24:46,467 --> 00:24:48,900
Are you really going to leave
Uncle Noah for Coleen's dad?

388
00:24:49,033 --> 00:24:49,967
Our dad.

389
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:52,433
Coleen, you're the only one
who calls him dad.

390
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:55,067
Mom, I'm begging you. Please.

391
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:57,167
Make up with Uncle Noah.

392
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:59,867
Because, Mom,I can never accept
your ex-husband.

393
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,133
Mom, you got fired from work?

394
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:04,100
What bad luck, really.

395
00:25:04,233 --> 00:25:07,567
It started when your dad's path
crossed with Felma.

396
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:09,467
Maybe that woman cursed us.

397
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:11,833
It's your dad's fault
that he met up with her.

398
00:25:11,967 --> 00:25:13,733
Why are you still defending him,
Mom?

399
00:25:13,867 --> 00:25:15,800
You're letting your relationship
with Uncle Noah fall apart

400
00:25:15,933 --> 00:25:17,067
just because of your ex.

401
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:18,833
Mom, you've already found
an angel.

402
00:25:18,967 --> 00:25:20,400
Are you in your right mind, Mom?

403
00:25:20,533 --> 00:25:22,167
Don't talk to me like that!

404
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:24,133
I need to find a job right away.

405
00:25:24,267 --> 00:25:25,900
But it'll be hard for me

406
00:25:26,033 --> 00:25:28,200
as long as I'm tied down
taking care of your dad.

407
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:29,100
What do you mean?

408
00:25:29,233 --> 00:25:31,333
I can no longer take care
of him.

409
00:25:31,467 --> 00:25:33,333
I have to bring him
to a nursing home.

410
00:25:33,467 --> 00:25:34,100
What?

411
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,433
No way! I'm not okay with that!

412
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,567
We have no choice.

413
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:39,400
And it's not up for your dad
to decide.

414
00:25:39,533 --> 00:25:42,433
I'll accept whatever
your decision is, Hazel.

415
00:25:42,667 --> 00:25:44,467
I have something to show you.

416
00:25:45,167 --> 00:25:46,433
It's a surprise.

417
00:25:48,067 --> 00:25:49,567
Hi, Dad!

418
00:25:51,033 --> 00:25:52,700
Dad, how are you?
